Technical Considerations
1. Scalability
Horizontal Scaling Strategy
• API Servers:
o Stateless design for easy horizontal scaling
o Load balancer distribution (ALB or equivalent)
o Auto-scaling groups based on CPU and request rate
o Target: 1000 concurrent users per instance
o Scale trigger: 70% CPU utilization
Database Scaling
• PostgreSQL:
o Read replicas for query distribution (ratio: 1 write, 2-3 read)
o Connection pooling (PgBouncer)
o Partitioning strategy for bookings table (by date)
o Prepared for sharding by geographic region (future)
• MongoDB:
o Replica sets for high availability
o Sharding by event_id for horizontal distribution
o Indexes optimized for query patterns
Caching Strategy
• Redis Cluster:
o Multiple nodes with replication
o Automatic failover
o Data partitioning across nodes
CDN for Static Assets
• CloudFront or equivalent
• Edge locations in EU for DACH region
• Cache invalidation strategy
• Versioned assets for cache busting
Load Balancing
• Application Load Balancer (ALB)
• Health checks every 30 seconds
• Sticky sessions for chat features
• SSL termination at load balancer
Capacity Planning
• Target: 10,000 active events simultaneously
• 100,000 concurrent users
• 50,000 bookings per month
• 1M API requests per day
2. Performance
Response Time Targets
• API endpoints (95th percentile):
o Read operations: < 200ms
o Write operations: < 500ms
o AI recommendations: < 2 seconds
o Payment processing: < 3 seconds
• Mobile app:
o Cold start: < 2 seconds
o Screen transitions: < 300ms
o Image loading: < 1 second (with placeholder)
• Web application:
o First Contentful Paint (FCP): < 1.8 seconds
o Time to Interactive (TTI): < 3.5 seconds
o Largest Contentful Paint (LCP): < 2.5 seconds
Optimization Techniques
• Client-Side Caching:
o HTTP caching headers (Cache-Control, ETag)
o Service Worker caching (PWA)
o Local storage for user preferences
o IndexedDB for offline data
• Lazy Loading:
o Images loaded on demand with intersection observer
o Code splitting for React components
o Pagination for large lists
o Infinite scroll for feeds
• Image Optimization:
o WebP format with JPEG fallback
o Responsive images (srcset)
o Image compression (80% quality)
o Thumbnail generation (multiple sizes)
o Progressive JPEG loading
• Database Optimization:
o Query optimization with EXPLAIN ANALYZE
o Composite indexes for common queries
o Materialized views for analytics
o Query result caching in Redis
• API Optimization:
o GraphQL for flexible data fetching
o Field-level response filtering
o Batch requests where appropriate
o Response compression (gzip/brotli)
Performance Monitoring
• Real User Monitoring (RUM) via Google Analytics
• Synthetic monitoring for critical paths
• Core Web Vitals tracking
• Mobile app performance metrics (Firebase Performance)
• Backend APM (Application Performance Monitoring)
3. Reliability
Uptime Target: 99.9%
• Maximum allowed downtime: 43.8 minutes/month
• Planned maintenance windows: Sunday 02:00-04:00 CET
• Zero-downtime deployments using blue-green strategy
High Availability Architecture
• Multi-AZ deployment (3 availability zones)
• Database replication across zones
• Load balancer health checks
• Automatic failover for critical services
• Circuit breaker pattern for external dependencies
Graceful Degradation Strategy
• Tiered Functionality:
1. Critical: Booking creation, payment processing (must work)
2. Important: Event browsing, chat (degrade to cached data)
3. Nice-to-have: AI recommendations, social sharing (fail gracefully)
• Fallback Mechanisms:
o AI recommendations → Fallback to rule-based suggestions
o Image CDN → Fallback to placeholder images
o Real-time chat → Fallback to polling mechanism
o Third-party auth → Fallback to email/password
o SMS notifications → Fallback to email only
Backup & Disaster Recovery
• Database Backups:
o PostgreSQL: Continuous archiving (WAL), daily snapshots
o MongoDB: Daily snapshots with point-in-time recovery
o Backup retention: 30 days
o Backup location: Different region than primary
o Automated backup testing weekly
• Recovery Time Objectives:
o RTO (Recovery Time Objective): 4 hours
o RPO (Recovery Point Objective): 1 hour
o Database restore time: < 2 hours
o Full system restore: < 4 hours
• Disaster Recovery Plan:
o Documented runbooks for common failures
o Quarterly DR drills
o Cross-region failover capability (post-MVP)
o Data replication to backup region
Incident Response
• PagerDuty integration for critical alerts
• On-call rotation for engineering team
• Incident severity levels (P0-P4)
• Post-mortem process for P0/P1 incidents
• Status page for user communication
Multi-Region Deployment (Future)
• Primary region: EU-Central-1 (Frankfurt)
• Secondary region: EU-West-1 (Ireland)
• Active-passive configuration initially
• Geographic routing based on user location
• Data residency compliance for GDPR
4. Security
OWASP Top 10 Vulnerability Protection
1. Broken Access Control:
o Role-based access control (RBAC)
o JWT validation on every request
o Resource-level authorization checks
o Principle of least privilege
2. Cryptographic Failures:
o TLS 1.3 for all connections
o Data encryption at rest (AES-256)
o Secure key management (AWS KMS or equivalent)
o No sensitive data in logs or error messages
3. Injection:
o Parameterized queries for all database operations
o ORM usage (Sequelize, Mongoose) to prevent SQL injection
o Input sanitization with DOMPurify
o NoSQL injection prevention
4. Insecure Design:
o Threat modeling during design phase
o Security requirements in user stories
o Secure-by-default configurations
o Separation of concerns
5. Security Misconfiguration:
o Automated security scanning in CI/CD
o Regular dependency updates
o Minimal permissions for service accounts
o Security headers (HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options)
6. Vulnerable and Outdated Components:
o Automated dependency scanning (Dependabot, Snyk)
o Monthly security patch reviews
o Software Bill of Materials (SBOM)
o Node.js and Python security advisories monitoring
7. Identification and Authentication Failures:
o Multi-factor authentication (optional for users, required for admins)
o Password complexity requirements
o Rate limiting on authentication endpoints
o Argon2 password hashing
o Session timeout (15 minutes inactivity)
8. Software and Data Integrity Failures:
o Signed releases with code signing certificates
o Integrity checks for third-party libraries
o Secure CI/CD pipeline
o Immutable audit logs
9. Security Logging and Monitoring Failures:
o Comprehensive security event logging
o Real-time security alerts
o Log correlation and analysis
o Integration with SIEM (future)
10. Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF):
o URL validation and allowlist
o Network segmentation
o No user-controlled URLs in backend requests
Regular Security Audits
• Monthly automated security scans
• Quarterly penetration testing
• Annual third-party security audit
• Bug bounty program (post-launch)
Data Encryption
• At Rest:
o Database encryption (PostgreSQL TDE, MongoDB encryption)
o S3 bucket encryption
o Encrypted backups
o Key rotation policy (90 days)
• In Transit:
o TLS 1.3 for all API communications
o Certificate pinning for mobile apps
o HTTPS enforcement
o No mixed content
Input Validation & Sanitization
• Server-side validation for all inputs
• JSON schema validation
• XSS prevention via output encoding
• Content Security Policy headers
• File upload validation (type, size, content)
CSRF/XSS Protection
• CSRF tokens for state-changing operations
• SameSite cookie attribute
• Content Security Policy
• X-XSS-Protection header
• HTML sanitization for user-generated content
API Security
• API Gateway with rate limiting
• Request signature validation
• IP allowlist for admin endpoints
• API key rotation for integrations
• OAuth 2.0 for third-party access
Mobile App Security
• Code obfuscation (ProGuard, SwiftShield)
• Certificate pinning
• Jailbreak/root detection
• Secure local storage (Keychain, Keystore)
• Biometric authentication for sensitive operations
Compliance
• GDPR compliance for EU users
• PCI DSS Level 1 (via Stripe)
• OWASP ASVS Level 2
• ISO 27001 preparation (future)
