User Experience: Seamless, intuitive flows with minimal friction
Visual Design: Modern, distinctive aesthetic with attention to detail
4. 5. 6. Performance: Fast, responsive, smooth interactions
Accessibility: Inclusive design for all users
Impact: Solves real problem with measurable outcomes
Polish & Attention to Detail
Micro-interactions
• Haptic feedback at key moments
• Smooth state transitions
• Loading skeletons match content
• Success animations celebrate user achievements
• Empty states guide next actions
Consistency Across Platforms
• Shared design language
• Platform-specific conventions respected
• Unified brand experience
• Consistent terminology and icons
Performance Optimization
• 60fps animations
• Instant feedback (<100ms)
• Optimized images and assets
• Minimal app size
Delightful Moments
• Booking confirmation celebration
• Achievement unlocks
• Personalized greetings
• Surprising helpful features
Progressive Web App (Post-MVP)
PWA Features
• Installable from browser
• Offline functionality with Service Workers
• Push notifications
• Add to home screen
• Full-screen immersive experience
PWA Requirements
• HTTPS everywhere
• Web app manifest
• Service worker registration
• Responsive and mobile-friendly
• Fast loading (< 3s)
Quality Assurance & Testing Strategy
Testing Pyramid
Unit Tests (70%)
• Individual functions and components
• API endpoint logic
• Database queries
• Utility functions
• Coverage target: 80%+
Integration Tests (20%)
• API integration with database
• Third-party service mocking
• Component interactions
• Payment flow end-to-end
End-to-End Tests (10%)
• Critical user journeys:
o Registration and login
o Event creation and questionnaire
o Package selection and booking
o Payment processing
o Social sharing
• Tools: Appium (mobile), Playwright (web)
• Run on staging environment
Testing Environments
Development
• Local development with Docker Compose
• Mocked external services
• Seeded test data
Staging
• Production-like environment
• Real integrations (sandbox mode)
• Automated deployment from main branch
• E2E test suite runs here
Production
• Live environment
• Real payment processing
• Monitoring and alerting
• Blue-green deployment strategy
Device & Browser Testing
iOS Devices (Physical & Simulator)
• iPhone SE (small screen)
• iPhone 14 Pro (standard)
• iPhone 15 Pro Max (large)
• iPad Air (tablet)
• iOS versions: Current and previous major
Android Devices (Physical & Emulator)
• Samsung Galaxy S22 (flagship)
• Google Pixel 6 (standard)
• Xiaomi Redmi (budget, large screen)
• Samsung Galaxy Tab (tablet)
• Android versions: 8.0 to current
Web Browsers (Desktop & Mobile)
• Chrome (latest 2 versions)
• Safari (latest 2 versions)
• Firefox (latest 2 versions)
• Edge (latest)
• Mobile Safari (iOS)
• Chrome Mobile (Android)
Performance Testing
Load Testing
• Simulate 1,000 concurrent users
• Measure response times at load
• Identify bottlenecks
• Tools: k6, JMeter
Stress Testing
• Push system to breaking point
• Measure graceful degradation
• Recovery time after stress
Spike Testing
• Sudden traffic increases
• Campaign launch simulation
• Flash sale scenarios
Security Testing
Automated Security Scans
• Dependency vulnerability scanning (Snyk)
• SAST (Static Application Security Testing)
• DAST (Dynamic Application Security Testing)
• Container image scanning
Manual Security Testing
• Penetration testing (quarterly)
• OWASP Top 10 validation
• Authentication bypass attempts
• Authorization testing
• Input validation testing
Accessibility Testing
Automated Testing
• axe DevTools
• Lighthouse accessibility audit
• WAVE browser extension
Manual Testing
• Screen reader testing (VoiceOver, TalkBack)
• Keyboard navigation testing
• Color contrast validation
• Text scaling testing
• Focus management validation
Beta Testing Program
Closed Beta
• 50-100 invited users
• Diverse user demographics
• Mix of iOS and Android
• Active feedback collection
• Crash reporting and analytics
Open Beta (Pre-launch)
• Public signup via TestFlight (iOS) and Google Play Beta (Android)
• 500-1,000 users
• Phased rollout
• In-app feedback mechanism
• Bug bounty for critical issues
Release Process
Version Numbering
• Semantic versioning: MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
• Example: 1.0.0 (MVP), 1.1.0 (new features), 1.0.1 (bug fixes)
Release Checklist
• [ ] All automated tests passing
• [ ] Manual regression testing completed
• [ ] Accessibility audit passed
• [ ] Performance benchmarks met
• [ ] Security scan clear
• [ ] Release notes drafted
• [ ] App Store screenshots updated
• [ ] Privacy policy and terms reviewed
• [ ] Rollback plan prepared
• [ ] Stakeholder approval
Phased Rollout
• 5% of users (Day 1)
• 25% of users (Day 3, if stable)
• 50% of users (Day 5)
• 100% of users (Day 7)
• Halt rollout if error rate > 0.5%
