• WCAG 2.1 AA standard
• Accessibility statement published
• Regular audits and updates
• User feedback mechanism for accessibility issues
App Store Requirements
• Apple App Store Review Guidelines compliance
• Google Play Developer Policy compliance
• Age rating: 17+ (social networking, user-generated content)
• Privacy labels and app permissions disclosure
• In-app purchase guidelines (if applicable)
Conclusion
This technical requirements document outlines a comprehensive, award-winning native iOS
and Android application architecture for Game-Over.app, with a subsequent web application
that mirrors the mobile experience. The platform leverages modern technologies, AI-powered
personalization, and relationship preservation principles to deliver a seamless, delightful
bachelor/bachelorette party planning experience.
By prioritizing native development for mobile platforms, focusing on performance,
accessibility, and security, and maintaining consistent design language across all touchpoints,
Game-Over.app is positioned to become the premier celebration planning platform in the
DACH region and beyond.
### 8. Participant feedback & communication
#### 8.1 Enhanced feedback collection
- Sharing options:
- Direct link
- WhatsApp integration
- SMS delivery
- Email invitation
- Clear messaging about feedback deadline
- Mobile-optimized feedback interface
#### 8.2 Advanced voting mechanism (not in MVP included)
- Real-time feedback status display for organizer
- Aggregate view of voting results
- Notification of voting completion
### 9. **Social Sharing & Community Features**
#### 9.1 Sharing capabilities
- **Event sharing via social media**
- **Recommendation sharing**
- **WhatsApp group integration**
- **Instagram story templates**
#### 9.2 Community features (not in MVP included)
- **Local activity recommendations**
- **User-generated content**
- **Review and rating system**
- **Community challenges**
- **Referral program**
### 10. Booking & payment flow
#### 10.1 Booking logic
- Two options:
1. Immediate booking by organizer after package selection
2. Booking locked until feedback window closes (24h)
- Organizer configurable setting
- Clear explanation of booking rules
- Reservation hold system during feedback period
#### 10.2 Payment integration
- Stripe API (version 2024-10-28.acacia) integration for credit card payments
- Secure payment processing with PCI DSS Level 1 compliance (via Stripe)
- Stripe Payment Intents for SCA compliance (3D Secure 2)
- Payment Methods Supported:
o Credit/Debit cards (Visa, Mastercard, American Express)
o Future (Post-MVP): Apple Pay, Google Pay via Stripe
- Enhanced cost-split calculator with service fee after booking:
o Equal split (including service fee)
o Custom split amounts
o Honoree exclusion option
- Payment tracking dashboard with service fee visibility
o Real-time payment status per participant
o Automated payment reminders (24h, 48h, 7 days before event)
o Partial payment acceptance
- Receipt generation and distribution via SendGrid email
- Stripe Connect for provider payouts (Future phase)
- Webhook integration for payment status updates
#### 10.3 Booking confirmation
- Email confirmation with:
- **Invoice PDF including service fee breakdown**
- Digital tickets/vouchers
- Itinerary summary
- Contact information
- Push notification with booking details
- Add to calendar functionality
- Booking reference number
### 11. Roles & permissions
#### 11.1 Organizer
- Full access to:
- Event management
- **Communication center**
- Booking and payments
- Financial information
- Guest list management
- Co-organizer assignment
- Ability to cancel or modify bookings
#### 11.2 Guest
- Limited access to:
- Event basic information
- **Structured communication and voting tools (not in MVP included)**
- **Budget transparency (their portion only)**
- Own feedback submission
- Activity details (once revealed)
- Complete guest list
- No access to:
- Full financial details
- Booking management
- Other participants' private information
#### 11.3 Bride/groom
- "Surprise View" with activities revealed only 1h before start
- Access to:
- Basic event information
- Timeline of activities (once revealed)
- No access to:
- **Detailed cost information**
- Complete guest list
- Planning details
#### 11.4 Provider (partner)
- Partner dashboard with:
- Calendar view of bookings
- Group size and requirements
- Revenue overview and projections
- Messaging channel with platform team
- Booking management tools
- Customer feedback access
### 12. Notifications & alerts
#### 12.1 Push & email notifications
- Triggers:
- New feedback submission
- **Budget transparency updates**
- Booking confirmations
- Payment reminders
- Activity updates
- Timeline changes
#### 12.2 In-app notifications
- Notification center with read/unread status
- Categorized notifications
- Action-required indicators
- Deep linking to relevant sections
- Future capability for real-time updates during event
### 13. Extensibility & security
#### 13.1 Modular codebase
- MVP geographic scope: Hamburg, Hannover, Berlin
- Package sizes: S, M, L only
- Architecture designed for expansion to:
- Full DACH region
- Additional package sizes
- Enhanced features
- API-first approach for future integration
#### 13.2 Data protection & encryption
- TLS 1.3 for all data in transit
- Encryption of sensitive data (payment details, personal information)
o AES-256 encryption at rest
o Database-level encryption (PostgreSQL TDE, MongoDB encryption)
- GDPR compliance
o Right to access, rectification, deletion, and data portability
o Data retention policy: 90 days for logs, 7 years for financial records
o Privacy by design and by default
- Regular security audits
o Quarterly penetration testing
o Annual third-party security audit
o Monthly automated vulnerability scanning (Snyk, Dependabot)
- Data minimization principles
- Secure password handling
o Argon2 password hashing algorithm
o Password complexity requirements: minimum 8 characters, uppercase,
lowercase, number
o Account lockout after 5 failed login attempts
- OWASP Top 10 vulnerability protection
- Security headers: HSTS, CSP, X-Frame-Options, X-XSS-Protection
- Rate limiting on authentication endpoints (5 requests/minute per IP)
- Session timeout: 15 minutes of inactivity
- Multi-factor authentication (optional for users, required for admins) - Post-MVP
## User Stories and Acceptance Criteria
### Authentication & Registration
#### US-101: User Registration
**As a** new user,
**I want to** create an account on Game-Over.app,
**So that** I can start planning a bachelor/bachelorette party without relationship
stress.
**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. User can register using email and password
2. User can register using OAuth (Facebook, Google, Apple)
3. System validates email format and password strength
4. System prevents duplicate email registrations
5. System displays appropriate error messages for invalid inputs
6. User receives confirmation email after successful registration
7. User must accept Terms & Conditions and Privacy Policy
#### US-102: User Login
**As a** registered user,
**I want to** log into my account,
**So that** I can access my events and planning tools.
**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. User can log in with email and password
2. User can log in using OAuth (Facebook, Google, Apple)
3. System validates credentials and shows appropriate error messages
4. User can select "Remember me" option
5. System redirects to last accessed page after login
### **Advanced Communication & Conflict Resolution**
#### US-301: Access Structured Communication Center
**As an** organizer,
**I want to** use structured communication tools,
**So that** I can avoid "Group Chat Chaos" and preserve relationships.
**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. Organizer can create topic-specific discussion threads
2. System separates voting discussions from general chat
3. Communication templates available for common scenarios (not in MVP included)
#### US-302: Resolve Conflicts Manually
**As an** organizer,
**I want to** access conflict resolution tools,
**So that** I can resolve disagreements without damaging friendships.
**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. System provides compromise suggestion templates (not in MVP included)
### **Budget Management & Transparency**
#### US-401: View Complete Budget Breakdown
**As a** participant,
**I want to** see complete budget transparency,
**So that** I can make informed decisions without financial surprises.
**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. **System displays service fee (10% or minimum €50) clearly and
separately**
2. **All costs broken down per person with service fee included**
3. **No hidden costs or surprise fees**
4. **Payment status visible to all participants**
5. **Refund policies clearly explained**
#### US-402: Manage Advanced Cost Splitting
**As an** organizer,
**I want to** split costs flexibly including service fees,
**So that** financial arrangements are fair and transparent.
**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. **Service fee can be split equally or assigned to organizer**
2. **Multiple splitting options available (equal, custom)**
4. **Honoree exclusion option available**
5. **Payment reminders automated**
### **Enhanced Voting & Feedback**
### **Social Sharing & Community**
#### US-501: Share Event Success
**As an** organizer,
**I want to** share successful events,
**So that** I can help others and build community.
**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. **Event sharing via social media platforms**
2. **Instagram story templates provided**
3. **Community gallery participation**
4. **Referral program integration**
5. **WhatsApp group sharing capabilities**
#### US-601: Track Voting Progress
**As an** organizer,
**I want to** monitor voting progress and conflicts,
**So that** I can address issues before they damage relationships.
**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. **Real-time voting status dashboard**
2. **Voting deadline enforcement**
### **Package Selection with Conflict Resolution**
#### US-701: Understand Complete Pricing
**As an** organizer,
**I want to** understand all costs including service fees,
**So that** I can make informed decisions.
**Acceptance Criteria:**
1. S-Package: €99 + service fee (10% or min €50) clearly displayed
2. M-Package: €149 + service fee (10% or min €50) clearly displayed
3. L-Package: €199 + service fee (10% or min €50) clearly displayed
4. Service fee calculation explanation provided to organizer
5. Total per-person cost calculated automatically including appropriate service fee